WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.020
Every integration in WashCentral has its own page under Settings.

p02
00:00:03.020 --> 00:00:05.391
The breadcrumb confirms where you are,

p03
00:00:05.391 --> 00:00:10.166
and the Integrations entry at the bottom of the left rail is the way in.

p04
00:00:10.166 --> 00:00:13.638
We start on Zoho Desk, the help desk connector,

p05
00:00:13.638 --> 00:00:17.262
because once you can read this page, you can read all eight.

p06
00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:18.743
Start at the top.

p07
00:00:19.372 --> 00:00:22.893
The badge next to the title says what the integration is for, help desk in this case,

p08
00:00:23.221 --> 00:00:24.445
and the pill beside it answers the client's first question.

p09
00:00:24.869 --> 00:00:27.958
Not Configured means nothing is wired up in this tenant.

p10
00:00:28.604 --> 00:00:35.082
One glance, and you already know the connection state.

p11
00:00:35.587 --> 00:00:37.831
Under the title, three small chips.

p12
00:00:38.585 --> 00:00:41.836
They name how WashCentral would talk to the vendor once connected.

p13
00:00:42.294 --> 00:00:45.026
Every integration page swaps in its own set,

p14
00:00:45.388 --> 00:00:47.918
so the chips become your fastest read on the method.

p15
00:00:48.427 --> 00:00:50.747
Watch them change as we tour the other pages.

p16
00:00:51.284 --> 00:00:53.952
Top right, two buttons, and we touch neither.

p17
00:00:55.311 --> 00:00:58.295
Test Connection fires a live call out to the vendor.

p18
00:00:59.686 --> 00:01:02.257
Edit Configuration opens the credential editor.

p19
00:01:02.466 --> 00:01:04.269
Both belong to an administrator.

p20
00:01:04.475 --> 00:01:06.493
Your job on this page is to read it,

p21
00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:09.200
and reading never requires a click up here.

p22
00:01:09.631 --> 00:01:10.716
Now the tile strip.

p23
00:01:11.337 --> 00:01:12.790
Four tiles summarize health:

p24
00:01:13.148 --> 00:01:18.194
the connection state, the data center, the org I-D, and which way data syncs.

p25
00:01:18.721 --> 00:01:22.419
Notice Connection reads Not set, which agrees with the pill above.

p26
00:01:22.771 --> 00:01:25.493
When those two match, you can trust the page's story.

p27
00:01:25.986 --> 00:01:27.718
Below the tiles, two tabs.

p28
00:01:28.313 --> 00:01:31.971
Settings, the one that's open, holds the live field values.

p29
00:01:32.338 --> 00:01:34.687
Instructions holds the vendor's setup steps,

p30
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:38.329
and we leave it closed today because its contents haven't been verified yet.

p31
00:01:39.037 --> 00:01:41.247
Everything we need sits on the Settings tab.

p32
00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:43.569
Scroll into the credentials group.

p33
00:01:44.315 --> 00:01:45.274
Client I-D, secrets, tokens, expiry.

p34
00:01:45.529 --> 00:01:46.214
Here is the rule that never bends:

p35
00:01:46.460 --> 00:01:48.040
you read the labels, never the values.

p36
00:01:48.578 --> 00:01:53.069
In this demo tenant the fields sit empty anyway,

p37
00:01:53.597 --> 00:02:01.360
but on a client's tenant a credential value never goes into a note, a screenshot, or a ticket.

p38
00:02:01.809 --> 00:02:02.639
Keep scrolling.

p39
00:02:03.340 --> 00:02:06.791
The remaining groups decide behavior once the connection is live.

p40
00:02:07.381 --> 00:02:08.655
General turns it on, Routing picks a default department and assignee,

p41
00:02:08.957 --> 00:02:11.645
Sync sets the direction, and Mapping ties Zoho's statuses to WashCentral's.

p42
00:02:12.100 --> 00:02:17.192
That is the whole anatomy.

p43
00:02:17.765 --> 00:02:23.680
The rest of this lesson is the same skeleton wearing different names.

p44
00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:25.589
Now Microsoft Entra I-D.

p45
00:02:25.589 --> 00:02:27.384
Same skeleton, different job.

p46
00:02:27.384 --> 00:02:31.823
The badge now reads single sign-on, the chips describe Microsoft's method,

p47
00:02:31.823 --> 00:02:37.480
and the tiles track the issuer, client I-D, and scopes instead of help desk fields.

p48
00:02:37.480 --> 00:02:41.885
One field worth knowing: the redirect U-R-I, with its Copy button,

p49
00:02:41.885 --> 00:02:45.279
is what an admin pastes into the identity provider.

p50
00:02:45.714 --> 00:02:46.280
Google, Okta, Cognito.

p51
00:02:46.565 --> 00:02:47.978
Three more providers, one layout.

p52
00:02:49.060 --> 00:02:51.168
Only the name and the method chips change from page to page,

p53
00:02:51.604 --> 00:02:54.726
and every one of them sits at Not Configured here.

p54
00:02:55.103 --> 00:02:57.692
Learn the Entra page and you have learned all four.

p55
00:02:58.402 --> 00:03:03.511
That is the payoff of the shared anatomy.

p56
00:03:04.047 --> 00:03:06.955
SCIM, pronounced skim, is the odd one out.

p57
00:03:06.955 --> 00:03:09.251
Instead of signing people in,

p58
00:03:09.251 --> 00:03:12.886
it creates and deactivates users automatically from the identity provider.

p59
00:03:12.886 --> 00:03:16.341
The tiles track its status and last event,

p60
00:03:16.341 --> 00:03:20.703
and the sync log below stays empty until provisioning events start arriving.

p61
00:03:21.184 --> 00:03:23.398
On to accounting. Open Sage.

p62
00:03:24.249 --> 00:03:27.189
The shape holds, but the fields turn financial.

p63
00:03:27.887 --> 00:03:32.285
The sync schedule tile shows a cron value because Sage posts on a timer,

p64
00:03:32.646 --> 00:03:34.972
two in the morning here, not on every sale.

p65
00:03:35.805 --> 00:03:38.120
And note the safety group's dry run flag,

p66
00:03:38.382 --> 00:03:41.614
a rehearsal switch that tests a sync without posting anything.

p67
00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:43.908
QuickBooks Online, the other ledger.

p68
00:03:43.908 --> 00:03:46.595
Same badge, same subtitle, different vendor.

p69
00:03:46.595 --> 00:03:51.815
Its credentials add a realm, which is QuickBooks' name for the company I-D,

p70
00:03:51.815 --> 00:03:53.277
alongside the usual tokens.

p71
00:03:53.277 --> 00:03:56.960
Sage and QuickBooks do one job through two doors,

p72
00:03:56.960 --> 00:04:01.280
the same pattern you just saw across the four sign-on providers.

p73
00:04:01.680 --> 00:04:03.878
Back to Zoho for the read that matters.

p74
00:04:04.268 --> 00:04:06.449
A client says the integration is broken.

p75
00:04:06.779 --> 00:04:08.341
You check three things in order: the status pill,

p76
00:04:08.564 --> 00:04:13.334
then Test Connection, remembering an admin runs it, not you,

p77
00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:15.725
then token expiry in the credentials.

p78
00:04:15.985 --> 00:04:20.000
That answers "is it connected?" from one page, without filing a bug.

